{
  "texts": [
    "Example polymer structures generated by those models are shown in Fig. 2c.",
    "The stars in the molecular structures indicate the two ends of polymers which are connected repeatedly later to form a longer polymer chain with about 150 atoms in the backbone for evaluation in MD simulation.",
    "In addition, we further compare the performances of these models by assessing their ability to replicate distributions of various polymer properties, including the length of the SMILES string, conductivity, and transference number.",
    "Among these properties, the transference number is the https://doi.org/10.1038/s41524-024-01470-9",
    "fraction of the total ionic charge carried by a particular ion species in the electrolyte."
  ]
}